text: Department of Homeland Security analysts find insufficient evidence citizens of 7 countries included in Trump's travel ban pose a terror threat DHS report cites 'insufficient evidence' that citizens of countries affected by Trump travel ban pose threat It asserts that citizenship is an 'unlikely indicator' of terrorism threats Said that just over half of 82 people determined to have been inspired by foreign terrorists to carry out U.S. attacks were U.S. citizens born in U.S. Others were from 26 countries led by Pakistan, Somalia, Bangladesh and Cuba DHS spokeswoman said report is incomplete, not final comprehensive review Trump said Friday a new edict would be announced soon Published: 21:48 GMT, 24 February 2017 | Updated: 05:48 GMT, 25 February 2017 149 shares
